event.description:
Jazz At The Vineyard A new Jazz Lifestyle Experience for 2016, this series of special Saturdays at Shelton Vineyards in the Yadkin Valley pairs wine tastings and vineyard tours with vintage evening jazz performances by top talent. Bring your lawn chair and reserve your ticket now for these special Jazz Experiences. July 9, 2016 Grammy Winner, Guitarist Earl Klugh celebrating 40 years Opening performance by Saxophonist Jeff Kashiwa Concert begins at 6 pm.... wine tastings begin at 2 pm Additional details: The vineyard will be open to concert guest starting at 2 pm. A wine tasting and tour is included in your ticket price. Wine tasting and tours will happen every half hour up until the concert begins at 6 pm. the concert will run until 9 pm. Saxophonist Jeff Kashiwa will open the show. **Event will go on rain or shine** (this is an outdoor event) *No outside food, coolers or tents* **Ticket includes wine tasting** No refunds or exchanges ABOUT EARL KLUGH: Earl Klugh: Celebrating 40 Years Earl Klugh will, by his own merits, become one of the most important voices on the guitar in the 70s. This album is clear evidence of what Im talking about. Throughout it, you will become thrilled by both his complete mastery of his instrument and his beautiful, sensitive reflections. Im especially excited by Vonetta, which was written by Earl, because it truly exemplifies the kind of musician he is one with a great sense of rhythm, harmony and feel I know that you will get as much pleasure out of listening to this album as I have had working with Earl Right on, Earl Klugh! George Benson, on Klughs self-titled debut Earl Klugh (1976) Since GRAMMY-winner Earl Klugh released his inaugural album in 1976, the Detroit-born master of the acoustic-classical guitar has become one of the most imitated icons of the instrument. He has released over 40 records, 24 of which have been on Billboards top-10 list of jazz albums and 6 of which have made it to the No. 1 slot. Klughs recordings have received 13 Grammy nominations (including one for his latest release, HandPicked) and his collaboration with pianist Bob James, One on One, walked away with the 1980 Grammy Award for Best Pop Instrumental Album. In 2016, Earl celebrates the 40th Anniversary of his debut album Earl Klugh (1976, Blue Note Records) with a very special catalogue of shows, highlighting selections from over 250 original compositions and featuring Klughs favorite standards, influences and collaborations from throughout his illustrious career. Ive been so fortunate to be able to create the music that Ive wanted to create, and work with some of the greatest artists of our time, says Klugh. Its hard to believe its been 40 years since that first record! You know, this one really caught me by surprise, reflects Klugh. When I look up, time has just flown by. But, Im still here, and Im still playing! Im just so pleased and happy to have the career Ive had so far. Ive met so many wonderful people, in and out of the musical realm. Im living a really wonderful life where you just have to pinch yourself sometimes, because there are so many things to be grateful for. www.EarlKlugh.com

Hello all, Here are some additional details for the wine event: The vineyard will be open for our guest to check in starting at 2:00 pm. Wine tastings and tours (which are included in your price) will begin at 2 pm and happen every half hour. (5 wines) The concert will begin at 2 PM with Jeff Kashiwa and then Earl Klugh. The concert will run until 9 pm. For the Al Jarreau Show, guest can begin arriving at 1 PM for wine tastings and the show will begin at 5 PM and run until 8 PM. Picnic baskets: Baskets are no longer available as we had to order them in advance. The Harvest Grill (Vineyard restaurant) will sell food during both events. menu will be sent as soon as its available. If you are interested in staying overnight, there is a Hampton Inn at The Vineyard. The Hampton Inn provides shuttle service to and from the venue throughout the afternoon and evening. If you are interested in a sponsor tent/table, please contact us at info@thejazzlifestyle.com Thank you! Tammy
event.title: Jazz At The Vineyard - Grammy Winning Guitarist Earl Klugh celebrating 40 years

Flaming Kitchen is a sweet traditional Szechuan cuisine and karaoke lounge located in Chinatown. Flaming Kitchen is a hidden gem in Chinatown that also offers special delicacies like Dim Sum.  No visit to Chinatown is complete without Dim Sum. The Sliced Pork with Spicy Garlic sauce is a true delicacy. The mouth watering cold dish has a piece of sliced pork bell wrapped around a slice of cucumber covered in a savory spicy garlic sauce.

Moreover, Flaming Kitchen also focuses on aesthetic presentation and freshness of the dining room. The beautifully designed modern décor is “East meets West” in a landmark building that over 100 years old. The interior features traditional woodcarving in Chinese patterns and there are two floors for seating and six LED TVs. All these things combined all make for a wonderful experience at Flaming Kitchen, so come down for an experience you’ll never forget!
